	)

	(text "Raspberry Pi 40-pin HAT\nConnector Pin Assignments\n\nPins 1,17: +3.3V\nPins 2,4: +5V\nPins 6,9,14,20,25,30,34,39: GND\nPin 8 (GPIO14/TXD): Pi UART TX → MSPM0 PA11 (RX)\nPin 10 (GPIO15/RXD): Pi UART RX ← MSPM0 PA10 (TX)\nPin 11 (GPIO17): PWR_EN → Q_PWR gate (P-MOSFET)\nPin 12 (GPIO18): TRIGGER → MSPM0 PB21 ‖ BNC\nPin 16 (GPIO23): SWCLK → MSPM0 PA19 ‖ J_SWD pin 2\nPin 18 (GPIO24): SWDIO → MSPM0 PA20 ‖ J_SWD pin 3\nPin 22 (GPIO25): NRST → MSPM0 NRST ‖ J_SWD pin 1\nPin 27 (GPIO0/ID_SD): HAT EEPROM SDA\nPin 28 (GPIO1/ID_SC): HAT EEPROM SCL"
		(at 155 30 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000001-0000-0000-0001-000000000001")
	)

	(text "MSPM0 Power Switch\n\nQ_PWR (DMG2305UX, P-MOSFET)\n+3.3V (Pi) → Source\nDrain → VCC_3V3_MCU\nGate: R_GATE (1kΩ) from GPIO17\n        R_PD (10kΩ) to GND\nDefault: gate LOW → MOSFET ON\nGPIO17 HIGH → power cycle MSPM0"
		(at 155 80 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000001-0000-0000-0001-000000000002")
	)

	(text "SWD Debug Header J_SWD (5-pin, 0.1\" pitch)\n\nPin 1: NRST\nPin 2: SWCLK (MSPM0 PA19)\nPin 3: SWDIO (MSPM0 PA20)\nPin 4: +3.3V (target power reference)\nPin 5: GND\n\nAlso connected to Pi GPIO23/24/25\nfor OpenOCD bit-bang (bcm2835gpio).\nWhen using external debugger, set\nPi GPIOs to input (high-impedance)."
		(at 155 120 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000001-0000-0000-0001-000000000003")
	)

	(text "BNC Trigger Interface\n\nJ_BNC center → TRIGGER net\nMSPM0 PB21 internal pull-up enabled\nActive-low, 10 ms debounce in firmware\nR_TERM (50Ω): DNP by default\nPi GPIO18 connected in parallel"
		(at 155 160 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000001-0000-0000-0001-000000000004")
	)

	(text "HAT EEPROM (AT24C256)\n\nRequired by Pi HAT spec.\nI2C address: A0=A1=A2=GND → 0x50\nInterface: ID_SD/ID_SC (Pi GPIO0/GPIO1)\n4.7kΩ pull-ups to +3.3V on SDA and SCL\nWP=GND (write enabled during programming)"
		(at 155 195 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000001-0000-0000-0001-000000000005")
	)

